column5: Same thing happened last year on the southwest portion of the lake, only to a lot of people  If it happens again down this way they'll charge you for the rescue
Been there done that, but that was Lake Simcoe scary yes.
Yep.. when your hole is plowing water there's an issue !!
That's normal stuff, Julie. For the next two weeks, starting tomorrow, we'll be seeing bad stuff happening. No one likes it but it's the way it is.
Does that mean that a large percentage of ice fishermen are a little slow?
Only the few silly enough to venture out now     I called it quits 2 weeks ago.

Does that make the others silly Bill.. or you overly cautious??  There's still lots of safe ice around... just not out on Lake Erie !!  If I had of had the time this weekend, instead of working, I'd be right beside Lloyd... drilling through 30 inches of ice!
